Reasoning: The paper deals with object detection using convolutional neural networks and proposes a new operator for mining contextual information. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions that the proposed method is trained end-to-end, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on various datasets, including Pascal VOC and Microsoft COCO, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper mentions the robustness of the proposed method to occlusion and adversarial attacks, indicating a focus on robotics (cs.RO) as well.
